course_metadata.title: Monitoring and managing energy use in buildings

content_chunks.content: This e-course focuses on the data-driven energy analysis of existing buildings, planning and assessing the impact of energy saving measures. The main aim is to provide the skills for effective buildings' energy-efficiency related consultancy for real estate owners and managers. The course is based on e-lectures and individual practical exercises based on measured data from existing buildings. Successful completion of online tests and individual exercises is required for completing the course.

Energy monitoring technology for building performance optimization - this course delivers data-driven methodologies for comprehensive building energy analysis and energy efficiency consultancy services. Technology for energy monitoring includes European energy directives compliance frameworks and energy legislation requirements for building performance assessment. The course covers residential building energy balance analysis and non-residential building energy consumption patterns for comprehensive building stock evaluation. Participants gain expertise in thermal energy monitoring systems and electric energy consumption tracking for holistic building performance measurement. The curriculum introduces energy data pre-processing techniques, energy use visualization methods, and qualitative energy analysis approaches for identifying optimization opportunities. Students develop skills in energy demand normalization processes and energy saving measures assessment for effective building energy consultancy. The course prepares professionals to provide data-driven energy efficiency recommendations to real estate owners and managers, implement energy monitoring strategies, and evaluate the impact of energy conservation measures using measured building performance data and advanced analytical techniques.
